parameters.description: the content of the file to QA

parameters.name: fileName
parameters.value:
<filename.extension> 

(url encoded)

-----
If the extension of the file is not recognised (currently .spdx, .json, and .xml) then a 200 with no content will be returned

parameters.name: fileContents
parameters.value:
<the contents of the entire sbom go here>

Make sure the entire field is URL encoded

parameters.name: fileNames
parameters.value:
["<fileName1.extension", "<filename2.extension>"]

Make sure to URL encode this entire string. 

If there are less fileNames than contents you will get a 500

The first SBOM passed is considered the reference SBOM which all of the other SBOMs will be compared to.

parameters.name: contents
parameters.value:
["<file1 contents go in here>", "<file2 contents>"]

The first SBOM passed is considered the reference SBOM which all of the other SBOMs will be compared to. 

There must be 2 or more SBOMs passed, 0 or 1 will get a 400

The contents should include the entire content of the files. Make sure to escape all \n (new line) characters in the SBOM before putting them the above JSON list and URL encoding the entire thing
